  "description": [
    "Court Proposal Put on Basis of Crisis Appeal by Roosevelt Held Answered by Tribunal in 1866 BY DAVID LAWRENCE PRESIDENT ROOSEVELT has appealed to the Nation in effect to give him the powers of a benevolent dictatorship His radio speech means that he does not believe either the Constitution or the Supreme Court should stand in the way of a free use of all govern mental power by a oneman gov ernment it the purpose Is de signed to benefit the average man Mr Roosevelts Underlying phil osophy is not new In the annals of government the world over but it is decidedly novel coming from a President of the United States David Lawrence Whether one agrees witn tne presi dents concept of his duty the Impor tant fact is that fortified by an enor mous majority in the last election he considers that he has the right to brush aside constitutional precedent and demand a Supreme Court which must virtually collaborate in the po litical management of the national Government Mr Roosevelts argument is that a great crisis prevails and that there isnt time for the normal processes of democracy This will come as a big lurprise to many"
  ],
